    {
        "info": "Cybercriminals Exploit Human Behavior for Access",
        "description": "Despite enhanced security infrastructure, cybercriminals continue to exploit human behavior as a gateway into organizations. This includes stealing valid credentials and logging in, which is often easier than breaking through perimeter defenses. AI-enabled social engineering allows attackers to scale tactics quickly and convincingly. Identity has become the enterprise's front door, but traditional responses like awareness training are insufficient. Reducing human-enabled risk requires systems and governance designed to anticipate error and limit its impact.",
